        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">The HVAC industry faces its worst labor shortage in decades. With 430,000 open positions and only 295,000 qualified candidates, smart contractors are rethinking everything about employee management. Here's how to build and keep a winning team in 2026.</p>

        <h2 id="labor-shortage-reality">The HVAC Labor Shortage Reality</h2>
        
        <p>The numbers tell a stark story. HVAC contractors report an average of 73 days to fill a technician position, up from 45 days in 2022. The shortage isn't just about quantity, it's about quality. Only 38% of new hires pass their first-year performance review, costing companies an average of $28,000 per failed hire.</p>

        <p>Three factors drive this crisis: retiring baby boomers (22% of the workforce), competition from other trades offering higher starting wages, and a cultural shift away from manual labor careers. Companies that adapt their hiring and retention strategies are not just surviving but growing at 15% annually while their competitors struggle.</p>

        <div style="background: #f8f9fa; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 2rem 0;">
